And he comes back to this word that he uses over and over and over this boasting of mine.

55:38.217 --> 55:44.063
The false teachers boast to exalt themselves and parade themselves.

55:45.664 --> 55:50.168
Listen, no one likes a person that can only speak of themselves.

55:52.851 --> 56:00.178
And Paul says this boasting of mine will not be silenced in the regions of a chaos because Paul is not boasting in himself

56:00.322 --> 56:14.704
He's boasting in the evidences of God's grace in the church, and he's boasting of his calling before God and the ministry to which God's called him, and he is boasting not in all of his fancy credentials.

56:15.024 --> 56:26.802
Paul will go on in chapter 11 to boast that he has sacrificially laid his life down for the church with absolutely nothing to gain in return.

56:28.450 --> 56:48.580
Friends, that's the sort of people around you that you can trust who humble themselves before God and are selfishly, sacrificially serving the people of God, the body of Christ and the people around them without intent for selfish gain.

56:48.600 --> 56:58.034
10 times in chapter 11, Paul boast of his humble, pure service before the Lord.

56:59.778 --> 57:03.483
And finally in verse 11, he says, and why?

57:03.523 --> 57:11.695
Why do I sacrifice myself on the altar of God's servant for your sake?

57:12.136 --> 57:17.002
And again, he says in verse 11, 11, because I do not love you.

57:17.042 --> 57:19.566
Is this why I do this?

57:20.828 --> 57:22.110
That's what you assume.

57:24.253 --> 57:28.018
And then he says, God knows I do.

57:28.194 --> 57:29.896
of a passionate response.

57:29.976 --> 57:31.778
God knows the truth of the matter.

57:32.039 --> 57:35.923
He knows my heart and he knows that I love you.

57:35.963 --> 57:54.546
Even if no one else is willing to be called to witness, God has proven his love through this church, through Paul's ministry, and his God himself loves his bride.

57:55.906 --> 57:58.609
is concerned for her spiritual deception.

57:58.649 --> 58:16.025
And as Paul puts forward faithful ministry before this church, she's called back to what we found last week, a sincere and pure devotion to Jesus Christ.

58:19.308 --> 58:25.234
May you this morning recommit yourself to the one that you have been bound to.

58:26.146 --> 58:36.958
May God give us wisdom and discernment to know and love Christ and to give and receive in faithful ministry.

58:38.620 --> 58:47.750
There's so many matters going on in our world today, in your family today, in our community today.

58:50.252 --> 58:55.538
But let's not leave here before we get to the heart of the matter.

58:57.122 --> 59:12.042
Are you walking in a sincere, a single-minded and pure or holy or blameless devotion to Jesus Christ?

59:12.182 --> 59:13.804
Is that your heart?

59:18.150 --> 59:20.393
Are you squirming because you can't wait to get out of here?

59:21.475 --> 59:25.400
Is your mind racing distracted by other things?

59:25.460 --> 59:26.802
Are there allurements?

59:27.682 --> 59:32.066
that are threatening to pull you away from the center that is here.

59:34.769 --> 59:46.720
Ladies and gentlemen, I want to warn you and myself and all of us, if you pull that thread that lies in the middle of the sweater, you will pull the rest of the sweater.

59:48.122 --> 59:56.850
This is the thread that's the engine in the heartbeat to the entire operation, sincere

59:56.994 --> 01:00:01.300
and pure devotion to Christ.

01:00:03.743 --> 01:00:25.010
Father, we love you and we thank you that you've loved us and we pray that you would bless and refresh and keep your people, that we would be faithful to you and all of the responsibilities and vocations and mission that you've given to us.

01:00:25.858 --> 01:00:30.901
Make us wise, give us discernment and change our hearts.

01:00:31.945 --> 01:00:34.738
In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

